Results.ReviewText:
Nescafe Original it the best instant coffee in the world. It tastes better than all the big brands in any country. Drinking 6 or more cups a day I think I should know, when I visit people and I'm offered a drink I'll have tea rather than risk another brand.
When I travel I always take Nescafe with me whether its in the UK or abroad.
Results.Title: Convenient and Ecofriendly

Results.ReviewText:
I have drank Nescafe original all of my life, and have always enjoyed it, although the red top jars seam to have a stronger flavour, not as mellow as the older brown top jar.
I don't  know if the recipe has changed or my taste buds have changed, but  definitely  different, but not in a bad way, and I will continue  drinking Nescafe
Results.Title: Different

Results.ReviewText: I have purchased Nescafe for as long as I can remember, the taste is just perfect for me,and I find it stores well and the price remains competitive. When making my husbnad up a flask for when he is on nights, the taste remains as it should too. My friends enjoy having a coffee with me, so I shall continue to be a Nescafe drinker!!
Results.Title: Nescafe Drinker of many years

Results.ReviewText: Ever since I was a child Nescafé has been the one stable coffee in my life. Yes, I have been lured to stray for the odd jar of 'that new and improved and allegedly smoother' young pretender. But I always come back to my Nescafé. Every holiday I have ever been on a little tub of those lovely brown granules has been in my luggage.
Results.Title: For nearly 50 years...

Results.ReviewText: I've tried most coffees over a number of years and still come back to Nescafé. Its  taste has certainly improved and it's the best way to start the day. It's still competitively priced and it's instant - I don't have to wait an age for my coffee to filter through a cafetière. I always travel with a jar of Nescafé in my suitcase.
Results.Title: Instant coffee with barista flavour

Results.ReviewText: I have tried a few coffees in my time. I always come back to Nescafe original. The smell when I open a fresh jar lets me know how great the coffee will taste. I'm never disappointed by the rich taste. The fact that I can now use the enviromentally friendly refill pouches means I always get a good feeling from drinking Nescafe.
Results.Title: Amazing aroma!

Results.ReviewText: I've been drinking Nescafe Original for over 35 years since my mum introduced me to it. I've tried every type of instant coffee since and nothing comes close. I'd even choose it over some of the high street coffee chains, I like it that much! Reliable, good value and great tasting. For instant coffee, you simply can't beat it.
Results.Title: My staple drink!

Results.ReviewText: I have been drinking nescafe original for over fifty years, tried many different types , but nescafe's strong blend and flavour is second to none, The smell and taste of that first cup in the morning is the perfect turbo boost to start off your day...yes I am a caffeine junkie,lol,but I cant think of a better way to get hooked
Results.Title: Unrivalled

Results.ReviewText: I never thought I'd buy this type of coffee, but I thought I'd step it up a notch and try something new; so I tried this product and I'm so pleased I did. You can really taste the quality and purity of this coffee. I don't think I'll ever be able to go back to anything else now. I'm hooked. It's a very rich and quality coffee.
Results.Title: Quality in a mug

Results.ReviewText: I'm the first to admit I'm not really a morning person and unless my day starts with a Nescafé original or two its not going to be a good day! There is always at least two jars in the cupboard just so there is no chance of running out of my morning ritual as my family knows the consequences of this action and it isn't pretty.
Results.Title: Mornings just aren't the same without nescafe.

ClientResponses.Response: Oh no, that's not good to hear but thank you for letting us know! We're making a note of everyone's comments regarding the changes.

Results.ReviewText: great offers on at the moment in the supermarkets, unfortunately since you have changed the taste i find the coffee very tasteless, even tho it states "original" the taste is not as it used to be, thus i do not now enjoy my nescafe, please go back to its original flavour,having being a nescafe drinker it tastes so different.
Results.Title: nescafe original

Results.ReviewText: the best way to wake up is to the aroma of a coffee placed next to you in bed, the senses tell you it's there the smell invigorates and you sit up take the steaming mug in your hands taking in the aroma before sipping on the rich roast that will kick start your day and bring a smile to your face, that's my Nescafé moment !
Results.Title: Waking to a new day

Results.Title: taste

ClientResponses.Response: It's disappointing you don't enjoy the changes we made to NESCAFÉ Original last year. Your comments are valuable to us Christine and have been shared with the rest of the team.

Results.ReviewText: We have drunk the Classic version (brown lid) for ever & bought the red lid as soon as it appeared on the shelves and the brown lid didn't. Absolutely vile - I got straight in touch with Nescafe & they responded in the same vein as the comments to others who have given negative reviews, that it had good reviews from "product testers" to which I responded "these cannot be genuine "classic" drinkers who have tested it but probably drinkers of inferior brands". I too have bought  every small 200g classic that I could find in bargain shops, sadly we are on our last jar and I cannot find any more. I will now have to change brands - who knows what to. I notice that the shelves at my supermarket are always full of the red top which suggests to me that it is not being bought by many people. It would be interesting to see some sales figures for the classic v double filtered original. Why not make both ? Surely the increased sales of the old classic will tell you something
Results.Title: If is aint broken don't fix it

Results.ReviewText: I HAVE TRIED SO MANY TIMES TO TRY OTHER COFFEES, BUT I COME STRAIGHT BACK TO NESCAFE ORIGINAL, I HAVE TOLD BEAN BLENDERS WHAT I LIKE IN DRINKING COFFEE BUT NO ONES COME CLOSE , TO THE WAY THE FULNESS WARMTH REAL COFFEE TASTE LIKE NESCAFE ORIGINAL LOVE IT SO MUCH THAT IF IM WITH OUT IT FEELS LIKE IM MISSING A GOOD FRIEND
Results.Title: NESCAFE ORIGINAL MY SECOND LOVE

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, thanks very much for getting in touch & leaving your feedback! We'll be making a note of your comments & passing them to the rest of the team.

Results.ReviewText: I have loved Nescafe Original for many years and feel so upset that you have changed the taste and ruined a great coffee. Not only does it taste terrible it also will not mix the same with milk as it used to.  Sorry but you have made a mistake and should return to the real original or you will loose all your customers.
Results.Title: What a mess

Results.ReviewText: My husband started to drink Nescafe in about  1955 when it was sold in tiny little 1/4 size tins. The coffee was powder then, but he stuck with Nescafe Original and loves the newer granules as he says there is a fuller flavour to it now. It is the only coffee in our house still. He converted me back in the early 1980's
Results.Title: Nescafe Original is the only coffee in our house.

Results.ReviewText:
We have only ever  used NESCAFE Original. THE best instant coffee.
I think I have found the best way to prepare a good cup of coffee.
Put a heaped teaspoon of Nescafe in a cup, add a little cold milk and stir thoroughly. Then pour on very hot water (not boiling) to make an excellent, authentic tasting cup of coffee.
Results.Title: The best instant coffee.

Results.ReviewText: I have been using Nescafe Original for many years. Normally , a long standing product eventually gets superseded by a better competitor. Not with Nescafe Original though. I have tried many others , but still come back to Nescafe every time as there is still nothing to touch it. It is still the undisputed number one.
Results.Title: Still the best.

Results.ReviewText: I have been drinking Nescafé decaf for years, especially at night to help me sleep. I find Nescafé decaf is the best tasting decaf I have tried. I don't notice any difference between ordinary Nescafé and Decaf Nescafé. Some decaf leave a bitter taste but not Nescafé. Thank you for helping me enjoy a coffee at night.
Results.Title: Tastes the same

Results.ReviewText:
Always buy Nescafe and have now converted everyone in the office!
Always a great cup of coffee which is full of flavour.
The great red mugs that came with it a few weeks ago were an added bonus. Although with the amount we drink we seem to have a huge stock of them now!
Wouldnt't change brand as none come close.
Results.Title: Full of flavour

Results.ReviewText: Just a single spoonful of coffee and you get a perfect cup of coffee every time, whether you add milk, sugar or just black, Nescafé tastes just right. It may cost a little more than some other brands, but it's worth it for the great taste and consistent high quality. And all in the time it takes to boil the kettle!
Results.Title: Perfect taste every time

Results.ReviewText: Over the years there has been so many new brands come to market but there still is only one that remains the Best Quality ,Best tasting coffee that is affordable ,found in all shops our lovely thirst quenching Nescafe .The quality never slips and is as good now as when it first hit the Shelves of our supermarkets.
Results.Title: Still one of the Best Coffee to buy

Results.ReviewText:
I have used Nescafé for as long as I can remember and I'm 46 now so we'll over 20 years. What can I say? Well it wakes me up of a morning, without my first cup I'm a dragon!! I have tried all the varieties available in Nescafé and they are all brilliant and flavoursome. 
Well done Nescafé keep up the good work!!
Results.Title: The coffee with wakeability

Results.ReviewText: I am no coffee connoisseur, and I thought I wasn't fussed between different brands. How wrong was I?! I tried something else and quickly reverted to Nescafe Original. Boosts my day. Great value for money, quick and easy to prepare - I especially enjoy with hot milk rather than water as a treat. Smooth and tasty.
Results.Title: Hard to beat.

Results.ReviewText: I've drank nescafe original for well over 20 years the new nescafe is much smoother and better tasting I drive for a living and drink over 2 ltrs of nescafe a day to keep me going.into get free tokens off diesel stations for free coster coffee and Starbucks and they don't come anywhere near as good as nescafe
Results.Title: Much better taste

Results.ReviewText: Every morning I come downstairs, feed the cat and then make my first cup of Nescafe. Then 10 minutes later, I make myself another cup of coffee. I really could not get through the day without my coffee, which I drink at regular intervals. I have tried other brands, but none of them taste as good as Nescafe.
Results.Title: Can't Get Through The Morning Without Nescafe!

Results.ReviewText: Good value for money excellent taste whether hot or cold as in Frappe Normally buy jars, with 3 in one and 2 in one to pack for holidays just in case stuck in an airport or not readily available. Just packed my original Nescafe coffee set and mugs which I bought in the 1970's - been treated like bone china.
Results.Title: Is there any other Coffee

Results.ReviewText:
I've always bought this coffee as i love its taste and smell. Its not too bitter so makes an enjoyable cup. 
The granules always look good and blend well when the water is added (no funny bits that don't dissolve)
Its good value, and I love the refill packs so i'm not throwing away big jars all the time
Results.Title: Great taste and smell.

Results.ReviewText:
All my life I've been a Nescafé drinker. During the day he took original Nescafé and at night decaffeinated Nescafé. Maybe I got used to that delicious taste of Nescafe, but it is what I have taken most of my life. I have tried different brands of instant coffee, but nothing like the great taste 
Nescafé
Results.Title: An excellent taste

Results.Description: A well-rounded, smooth coffee with a rich aroma.
